N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 332.6 - If military voter appears personally

State Regulations

In the event that any military voter personally appears to
register at any board of elections before, during or subsequent to central
registration, such military voter shall be furnished with an application (Form

No. 1)
[see Appendix 2, infra] for
completion by him and his name entered in the register of voters or on the
registration records and copy of such Form No. 1 must be forwarded to the
division. Notes
